Student number: GRDDAN017

REQUIREMENTS:
Have installed GLEW, SDL2, and GLM
Debian based Linux:
sudo apt install libsdl2-dev
sudo apt install libglew-dev
sudo apt install libglm-dev

RUN:
Linux - Enter make and then make run into the console in the root directory.

CONTROLS:
1. To turn on and off second light source press o.
2. To move the camera use the arrow keys. To orbit about the z axis use d and f keys.
3. To reset the position of the camera press r.
4. To increase and decrease the orbiting speed of the earth, use 1 and 2 keys.
5. For the moon, use 3 and 4.
6. To pause and unpause press p.
7. Quit with escape.

MASTERY:
1. Added extra planets (Venus and Mars) and adjusted how planets orbit sun to be more realistic.
2. Added a skybox.
3. Earth texture shows city lights when it's night time.

Resources used:
- part 1:
    https://learnopengl.com/Getting-started/Transformations and lecture slide set 4 slides 41 to 43 - Transformations in OpenGL
    https://jsantell.com/model-view-projection/ - Model View Projection

- part 2:
    https://learnopengl.com/Getting-started/Textures - Textures
    https://learnopengl.com/Getting-started/Camera - Camera
    https://learnopengl.com/Lighting/Basic-Lighting - Phong lighting
    https://learnopengl.com/Advanced-OpenGL/Cubemaps and https://opengameart.org/content/space-skyboxes-0 - skybox tutorial and skybox texture
    https://www.solarsystemscope.com/textures/ - other planet textures (used Venus, Mars, Earth day, Earth night)
    https://jaxry.github.io/panorama-to-cubemap/ - to create cubemaps images from regular images